<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">647.116/249a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Sydney</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-18T18:00:00-05:00">November 18, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Representative Maas of Minnesota has brought to me a letter from
                                Brandtjen and Kluge regarding shipments of printing presses which
                                have arrived at Sydney, Melbourne and Adelaide and stating that
                                their agents, S. Cooke Proprietary Limited of Melbourne, have been
                                unable to obtain entry permits.</p>
                            <p>I would like your opinion whether the special circumstances of these
                                machines having already been unladen in Australia might not, upon
                                special representations being made by you, be given consideration.
                                In general, do you think that special representations in specific
                                cases would be of avail in securing import permits.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>